result.execSummary:
The defendant Calvin D Montanaze-Brown was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Calvin D Montanaze-Brown in court with attorney Jeffrey Norman Jensen.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

As to Count 1:
The Court ordered the defendant to serve 55 days in the House of Corrections with Huber release for work and school, with credit for 1 day time served. Court stayed the sentence, and ordered the defendant to report to the House of Corrections by 11/13/2015 at 5:00pm.

As to Count 3:
Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 36 months in the Wisconsin State Prison, consecutive to the sentence ordered in Count 1.  Court ordered 18 months Initial Term Of Confinement and 18 months Extended Supervision.  Court found defendant not eligible for Challenge Incarceration or Earned Release Programs.  The Court stayed the sentence, and placed the defendant on 3 years probation.  The Court ordred the probabtion to run concurrent to the sentence ordered in Count 1.

Conditions of Probation/extended supervision:
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- No contact with victim.
- No contact with firearms.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- Provide a DNA sample.

Court ordered that the defendant pay all costs and surcharges associated with both Counts 1 and 3 in this case, including the DNA and domestic violence surchages. The Court also ordered the defendant to pay all supervision fees.
